name: Wink Stamp Long Waterproof Wing Eyeliner Stamp & Pen
about: What it is:A double-ended wing stamp and liquid pen liner that is smudgeproof, long-lasting, and waterproof, giving you a super easy winged eyeliner look every time..Highlighted Ingredients:- Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Fruit Extract: Contains moisturizing and nourishing properties..Ingredient Callouts:Free of sulfates SLS & SLES. It is also gluten-free..What Else You Need to Know:This easy-to-use wing stamp and liquid liner pen is available in an ultra-long stamp or original stamp set to get your best-winged eyeliner. Use Wink Stamp Original to create a classic eyeliner look or Wink Stamp Long for a dramatic eye look. This set is long-wearing, smudgeproof, and waterproof.
ingredients: -Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Fruit Extract: Contains moisturizing and nourishing properties..-Camellia Sinensis (Green Tea) Leaf Extract: Contains skin-protecting properties..-Camellia Sinensis (Black Tea) Leaf Extract: Contains skin-balancing and protecting properties...Wing Eyeliner Pen:.Aqua/Water/Eau, Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer, Propylene Glycol, Black 2 (Ci 77266), Alcohol, Pentylene Glycol, Styrene/Acrylates/Ammonium Methacrylate Copolymer, Beheneth-30, Butylene Glycol, Acrylates/Octylacrylamide Copolymer, Phenoxyethanol, 1,2-Hexanediol, Aminomethyl Propanol, C11-15 Pareth-7, Caprylyl Glycol, Sodium Laureth-12 Sulfate, Tetrasodium Edta, Ethylhexylglycerin, Potassium Sorbate, Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Fruit Extract, Camellia Sinensis (Green Tea) Leaf Extract, Camellia Sinensis (Black Tea) Leaf Extract...Wing Eyeliner Stamp:.Aqua/Water/Eau, Propylene Glycol, Black 2 (Ci 77266), Acrylates/Ethylhexyl Acrylate Copolymer, Styrene/Acrylates/Ammonium Methacrylate Copolymer, Alcohol, Pentylene Glycol, Beheneth-30, Butylene Glycol, Acrylates/Octylacrylamide Copolymer, 1,2-Hexanediol, Phenoxyethanol, Laureth-21, Aminomethyl Propanol, C11-15 Pareth-7, Caprylyl Glycol, Sodium Laureth-12 Sulfate, Tetrasodium Edta, Ethylhexylglycerin, Potassium Sorbate, Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Fruit Extract, Camellia Sinensis (Green Tea) Leaf Extract, Camellia Sinensis (Black Tea) Leaf Extract.
how_to_use: Suggested Usage:.Stamp: .-Shake well before use..-Position the wing-shaped stamp at the outer edge of the eye..-Press down firmlyu2014the wing should connect to the lower lash line, creating one continuous line...Line: .-Shake well before use..-Use the eyeliner pen to draw along the lashes..-Connect the wing. .-Repeat on the other side.

reviews.review_buyer_description: Brown eyes, Deep skin tone, Combination skin
reviews.review_text: Kaja Beauty recently received a complimentary Wink Stamp Wing Eyeliner Pen and Stamp Long. This two piece set promises a dramatic winged liner look in a matte black, waterproof finish. The Wing Eyeliner Pen is slim, with a thin felt tip that comes to an ultra fine point. It provides excellent precision and is particularly useful for my tear duct area, which I like to wing as well. The pen dispenses a good amount of liquid and allows for a smooth application with no skipping. For a wider line, I find it best to outline it and fill it in, keeping it a single, thin layer, as the liner can crack or flake if itu2019s too thick. Itu2019s more of a satin finish than matte; itu2019s not glossy, but thereu2019s a definite sheen. It wears very well, staying put until I take it off. Itu2019s also quite easy to remove for a waterproof formula. It comes off with anything oily, so the cleansing balms and oils I use work well and I donu2019t need a separate remover. The stamp is two-sided, with a wing stamp for the left and right eye. You just line up the wing where you want it and press, then connect it with the liner pen. The act of stamping and lining is really simple. My problem is with lining them up evenly, and neither my hooded lids nor the fact that one of my eyes is larger than the other makes it any easier. I kind of wish the stamps were in the caps, so I could line them up in the mirror at the same time. I tilt the stamps upward for a more dramatic wing. As a typical cat eye, they arenu2019t that big or bold on my already slightly catty eye shape. All in all, I think this liner is cute for a beginner. If I got it again itu2019d be for the liner. The stamp is cool on days when my hand is shaky, but I can otherwise crank out a wing with about the same amount of fiddling, so Iu2019m not sure Iu2019ll reach for it that often. I love the ultra thin liner, though, for its smooth and precise application.

reviews.review_text: I received this as a complimentary from Kaja. The Kaja wink stamp is truly amazing. it's a game-changer and incredibly easy to use. The stamp comes with labels for left and right, ensuring a hassle-free application for the perfect winged eyeliner every time. Not only does it provide a flawless wing, but it also boasts long-wearing capabilities, meaning your stunning eye look will last all day without smudging or fading. Additionally, the wink stamp adds a beautiful glow to your overall appearance, making your eyes pop with a captivating radiance.  The product comes in two convenient pieces: the Double-ended Wing Stamp and the Liquid Eyeliner Pen. Having both of these in one package is a dream come true for makeup enthusiasts like me. Not to mention, the fact that it's vegan and made with natural ingredients is a huge bonus. Knowing that I'm using a cruelty-free and eco-friendly product only adds to my love for the Kaja wink stamp.  Using the wink stamp has genuinely become one of my favorite parts of my daily beauty routine. It brings an element of fun and creativity to my makeup application, allowing me to experiment with different wing styles and intensities. Whether I want a subtle, everyday look or a dramatic, bold wing for a special occasion, the Kaja wink stamp never disappoints. Its user-friendly design and impressive results make it a staple in my makeup collection, and I can confidently recommend it to anyone looking to achieve flawless winged eyeliner effortlessly.  In conclusion, the Kaja wink stamp has exceeded all my expectations, and I can't imagine my makeup routine without it. Its ease of use, long-lasting formula, and ability to add a radiant glow to my eyes make it a must-have for every makeup lover. Whether you're a makeup novice or a seasoned pro, this product will elevate your eye game and make you fall in love with winged eyeliner all over again.

reviews.review_title: TRIED to love it; Just couldn't.
reviews.review_buyer_description: Hazel eyes, black hair, Combination skin
reviews.review_text: I received this complimentary from kajabeauty and I was hoping to love this since it would simplify my eyeliner (my wing always get bigger and bigger trying to match them) but after multiple tries, I just couldn't.  First, it comes with 2 pens, the wing stamp pen and a standard liner pen. I loved that there was a left and right stamp so it wouldn't just be one generic triangle.  The shape is great and it has a nice swoosh. The problem with the shape is in the side that hits your skin; It's perfectly flat while the area around your eye is curved. That means that when you stamp, the center hits first and you have to press it down more for the ends to hit. That gives me a big splotch in the center that I have to fix.  When I tried out the eyeliner pen to finish the look, it wasn't as wet as the stamp and when I tried going over areas more than once, it removed the pigment underneath. It was just a mess.  On top of that, it's supposed to be waterproof and smudgeproof but it's not. The area that I practiced on my hand wiped clean with just water, even after sitting for a while and drying down.   When I did manage to complete a look with it, it started flaking after a few hours. This formula is NOT IT. I would have managed to make it work if the formula was good, but it was terrible.
